OL,3,CStarmer's authority shaken by defence
OL,4,Csecretary's exit over military funding
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer's beleaguered
OL,7,Fpremiership has been shaken to its
OL,8,Fcore by the shock resignation of John
OL,9,FHealey as defence secretary over a
OL,10,Fdispute about long-term funding for
OL,11,Fthe military.
OL,13,FMr Healey was joined in his exit from
OL,14,FGovernment by armed forces minister Al
OL,15,FCarns, as well as two parliamentary
OL,16,Faides, heaping pressure on the Prime
OL,17,FMinister, who is already facing the
OL,18,Fthreat of a leadership challenge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1781229799
OL,3,CStarmer's authority shaken by defence
OL,4,Csecretary's exit over military funding
OL,6,FIn a letter announcing his decision,
OL,7,FMr Healey suggested Sir Keir had been
OL,8,F"unable" to overrule Chancellor Rachel
OL,9,FReeves in meeting the amount of cash
OL,10,Fwhich military officials had hoped for
OL,11,Fin the Defence Investment Plan (Dip).
OL,13,FThe Dip, a blueprint for how the armed
OL,14,Fforces will be funded into the future,
OL,15,Fhas been long delayed because of
OL,16,Fwrangling between the Ministry of
OL,17,FDefence (MoD), the Treasury, and No 10.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1781229799
OL,3,CStarmer's authority shaken by defence
OL,4,Csecretary's exit over military funding
OL,6,FThat all came to a head on Thursday
OL,7,Fwith Mr Healey's announcement, in
OL,8,Fwhich he also warned the Prime
OL,9,FMinister that without a Dip that
OL,10,F"meets the moment" he would be "forced
OL,11,Fto make decisions" that "could make
OL,12,Four country less safe".
OL,14,FMr Carns meanwhile said he would not
OL,15,Fbe able to "defend a level of
OL,16,Finvestment I know to be inadequate to
OL,17,Fthe task" if he remained as a minister.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@RO]rD@`OUsD@RO]sD@YOUtD@VO]wD@
OL,26,ALOUyD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
